					<description><![CDATA[<p>Series F Funding Strengthens AI Observability Expansion Coralogix Raises $200M marks a major milestone for the Boston based observability platform. The company builds AI driven tools for monitoring modern software</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/coralogix-raises-200m-to-scale-ai-native-observability-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Coralogix Raises $200M to Scale AI Native Observability Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Series F Funding Strengthens AI Observability Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix Raises $200M marks a major milestone for the Boston based observability platform. The company builds AI driven tools for monitoring modern software systems. The Series F round was co-led by Advent, CPPIB, and Greenfield. Brighton Park Capital also participated in the financing round.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix Raises $200M brings total funding to $550 million. The round follows the company’s rapid Series E raise just eleven months earlier. The valuation reached approximately $1.6 billion post money. Investor demand reflects strong confidence in AI infrastructure platforms.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company serves more than 5,000 enterprise customers globally. These include IBM, Tradeweb, and JFrog. Coralogix provides real time observability across logs, metrics, and traces. It helps organisations manage complex software environments at scale.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Agent Olly Powers Real Time System Intelligence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix Raises $200M supporting expansion of its AI native observability engine. The platform uses a streaming analytics system for large scale telemetry data. It processes petabytes of unstructured logs and system signals in real time. This removes the need for traditional sampling methods.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the centre of the platform is an AI agent named Olly. Olly investigates system behaviour and identifies root causes automatically. It operates alongside CLI and MCP interfaces for advanced workflows. These tools allow engineers and AI systems to interact with production data directly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s schema free architecture supports massive data ingestion. It enables enterprises to retain full fidelity telemetry data. This reduces blind spots in system monitoring and incident response. It also improves long term analysis of system performance trends.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix says more than half of enterprise users now interact with AI driven interfaces. Engineers increasingly rely on conversational and agent based tools. Traditional dashboard usage is gradually declining across customer deployments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The shift reflects broader adoption of AI powered software systems. These systems now generate more complex telemetry data than legacy tools can handle. Coralogix is positioned to support this new operational environment.</span></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise Growth and Competitive Observability Landscape<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202365" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202365" class="size-full wp-image-202365" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-showcases-a_u_hzf6aSWLCYjBt6dpys3Q_03zvuH94QjuSoa1aEC7TUQ.png" alt="AI observability platform analyzing real-time enterprise telemetry data with autonomous system monitoring" width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202365" class="wp-caption-text">Coralogix strengthens its position in AI-driven observability as enterprises shift toward automated monitoring and agent-based workflows. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix Raises $200M strengthens its position in the global observability market. The company operates in a competitive sector alongside Datadog, New Relic, and Splunk. These firms are also integrating AI into monitoring and operations workflows. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix reports strong commercial momentum across enterprise clients. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Revenue has grown more than sixty percent over the past year. The company also has around thirty customers spending over one million dollars annually.  </span><span style="font-weight: 400">It surpassed one hundred million dollars in annualised revenue previously. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform is used across financial services, media, retail, and cloud native industries. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It supports mission critical applications in production environments. The system is designed for high scale distributed computing infrastructure. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Ariel Assaraf said AI is reshaping enterprise observability workflows. He noted that engineers increasingly rely on AI assistants instead of dashboards. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He also highlighted growing demand for CLI and agent based operations. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">The company employs more than 600 people globally. It maintains a strong presence in the United States, Israel, and India. Its India office serves as a major engineering and regional operations hub.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/flok-health-raises-12-5m-ai-healthcare/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok Health Raises $12.5M to Scale AI Healthcare Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>AI Infrastructure Shift Drives Next Generation Observability</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix Raises $200M as enterprises adopt autonomous AI systems at scale. These systems require continuous monitoring and real time troubleshooting capabilities. Traditional observability tools struggle with increasing data volume and complexity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s infrastructure is built for full fidelity telemetry ingestion. It avoids sampling limitations that reduce visibility in legacy systems. This allows enterprises to analyse complete operational data streams. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix is expanding its agentic AI capabilities across its platform. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This includes deeper integration of Olly and automated investigation tools. It also includes CLI based workflows for engineering teams. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will also support expansion of its schema free telemetry data lake. This infrastructure enables real time processing and long term data retention. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It supports both human and AI driven analysis of system behaviour. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix is positioning itself as a core layer in AI driven infrastructure. The company believes observability will evolve into business intelligence for AI systems. It aims to support both human engineers and autonomous agents. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The firm is also expanding global enterprise adoption across regulated industries.  </span><span style="font-weight: 400">These include fintech, cybersecurity, and cloud infrastructure sectors. It is targeting organisations transitioning away from </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/legacy" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">legacy</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> monitoring tools. The company says it does not require additional funding at this stage. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It is focused on profitability and long term operational discipline. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">Leadership has also indicated preparation for public company readiness. Coralogix continues to build infrastructure for the AI operational era. Its platform is designed for systems where machines increasingly monitor and manage themselves.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/coralogix-raises-200m-to-scale-ai-native-observability-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Coralogix Raises $200M to Scale AI Native Observability Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
