					<description><![CDATA[<p>Gigaton has raised $26 million in a Series A funding round. The capital injection is intended to expand the company&#8217;s autonomous process control platform across the world’s most energy-intensive industries,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/gigaton-raises-26m-to-transform-industrial-control/" data-wpel-link="internal">Gigaton Raises $26M to Transform Industrial Control</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://gigaton.co/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Gigaton </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised $26 million in a Series A <a href="https://ventureburn.com/imu-biosciences-secures-53m-to-advance-immune-tech" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">funding</a> round. The capital injection is intended to expand the company&#8217;s autonomous process control platform across the world’s most energy-intensive industries, directly targeting the high costs and heavy carbon footprints of manufacturing foundation materials like cement, steel, glass, and chemicals.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financing round was led by Plural, with strong participation from 2150, Semapa Next, and an elite group of returning climate-tech and academic investors. These include Planet A Ventures, Cambridge Enterprise Ventures, Clean Growth Fund, and the UCL Technology Fund. The fresh $26 million brings Gigaton’s total institutional capital raised to date to over $35 million.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Overturning Decades of Manual Calibration</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Heavy industrial manufacturing accounts for roughly one-quarter of all global energy consumption. Despite the staggering scale of these operations, a vast majority of the world&#8217;s processing plants, steel mills, and kilns rely on software architecture built decades ago. These legacy systems depend heavily on continuous manual intervention by human operators sitting in control rooms to adjust baseline inputs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This manual approach has been stressed to the breaking point by modern market pressures. Industrial plants are aggressively moving away from predictable fossil fuels like coal to alternative, highly volatile fuel mixes, including solid recovered fuel, to meet tightening environmental mandates. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_202359" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202359" class="wp-image-202359" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Gigaton.jpeg" alt="Gigaton" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-202359" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Gigaton</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These alternative energy sources have a very high variation in moisture content and calorific value. This makes stable manual operation almost impossible. The consequence is systemic process instability, skyrocketing operating costs and millions of tonnes of avoidable carbon emissions.</span></p>
<div>
<div data-test-render-count="1">
<div class="group">
<div class="contents">
<div class="group relative relative pb-3" data-is-streaming="false">
<div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8">
<div>
<div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">University College London and the University of Cambridge jointly spun out Gigaton in 2020. It spent years embedded alongside control room operators to build a platform that directly replaces rather than sits on top of parts of this legacy software stack.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/imu-biosciences-secures-53m-to-advance-immune-tech" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> IMU Biosciences Secures $53M to Advance Immune Tech</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">An AI Autopilot for the Factory Floor</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Gigaton’s platform operates deep within a factory’s core infrastructure as a self-learning autonomous control system. Using advanced deep learning algorithms, the platform creates a highly accurate, real-time digital simulation of the active manufacturing process.</span></p>
<div>
<div data-test-render-count="1">
<div class="group">
<div class="contents">
<div class="group relative relative pb-3" data-is-streaming="false">
<div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8">
<div>
<div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Before any physical facility change, the AI forecasts the precise kinetic and thermodynamic outcome of an action. It then autonomously and continuously calibrates the core machinery variables, including kiln speed, oxygen flow, and multi-component fuel ratios to maintain an optimal equilibrium.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The economic and climate returns of the technology have already been validated at scale. Top-tier global building material conglomerates, including Adani Cement, Heidelberg Materials, Holcim, and Mannok Holdings, have fully deployed Gigaton&#8217;s software. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform is currently generating between $1 million and $3 million in annual energy savings per individual plant while slashing roughly 30,000 tonnes of CO2 emissions annually per facility, the environmental equivalent of taking thousands of cars off the road.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Global Scaling and Sector Expansion</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new Series A capital will back an aggressive roadmap designed to scale Gigaton&#8217;s environmental impact to a metric gigaton scale. Structurally, the firm is utilising the funds to execute a fivefold expansion of its engineering and deployment teams.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While the company has historically focused its autonomous controls on the global cement manufacturing sector, the fresh funding will immediately fuel product development to adapt its core deep-learning simulation models to other continuous-process heavy industries. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Gigaton has already initiated development partnerships to transition its real-time AI control architecture into global steel furnaces, glass fabrication lines, and chemical processing facilities, aiming to transition them toward automated, highly optimised dark plants that can run efficiently around the clock.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/gigaton-raises-26m-to-transform-industrial-control/" data-wpel-link="internal">Gigaton Raises $26M to Transform Industrial Control</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
