		<title>Westmag Raises $11M to Expand Drone Motor Production</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/westmag-raises-11m-to-expand-drone-motor-production/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 15:43:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=202349</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Westmag has raised $11 million in a Series A funding round to grow its production of next-generation electric motors for UAVs. This funding will address the Western aerospace supply chain&#8217;s</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/westmag-raises-11m-to-expand-drone-motor-production/" data-wpel-link="internal">Westmag Raises $11M to Expand Drone Motor Production</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://westmag.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Westmag </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised $11 million in a Series A </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/imu-biosciences-secures-53m-to-advance-immune-tech/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round to grow its production of next-generation electric motors for UAVs. </span>This funding will address the Western aerospace supply chain&#8217;s Achilles&#8217; heel: dependence on foreign-produced propulsion parts.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by Shield Capital, a venture fund focused on national security and dual-use technologies, with participation from established seed investor Point72 Ventures, Cercano Management, and a handful of other investors. </span>The company will use the $11 million to expand its automated manufacturing plant in Southern California, keeping pace with growing contracts.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Overcoming the Rare-Earth Obstacles</span></h2>
<p>Aerospace engineers and materials scientists founded Westmag in 2023 to address an ongoing engineering and geopolitics headache. Drone motors depend 100% on neodymium permanent magnets, whose supply chains are centralised outside the West, putting Western drone makers at risk.</p>
<div id="attachment_202350" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202350" class="size-full wp-image-202350" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Westmag.jpg" alt="Westmag" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-202350" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Westmag</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Westmag&#8217;s innovation is the proprietary electromagnetic framework and the superior stator/coil design. </span>Notably, through a redesign of motor geometry and flux paths, the company has built electric propulsion systems that outperform typical UAV power-to-weight ratios while minimising rare earth mineral use.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We didn&#8217;t just want to build a better motor; we needed to build a more resilient one,&#8221; said Elena Vance, co-founder and CEO of Westmag. &#8220;The drone industry has scaled incredibly fast, but its foundational hardware architecture is built on a single point of failure. This funding allows us to decouple high-performance drone manufacturing from volatile supply chains, ensuring our commercial and government partners have a reliable, domestic source of propulsion.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/imu-biosciences-secures-53m-to-advance-immune-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">IMU Biosciences Secures $53M to Advance Immune Tech</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Moving From Prototype to High-Rate Production</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The capital arrives at a major operational pivot point for Westmag. </span>After rigorous field testing with tier-one defence contractors and logistics operators, the company is shifting from low-rate production to high-volume assembly.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $11 million injection will be weaponised across three core operational pillars:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Facility Automation:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Implementing advanced robotics and automated winding machinery at Westmag&#8217;s San Diego facility to increase production throughput by an estimated 500% over the next twelve months.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Workforce Scaling:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Expanding the company&#8217;s engineering, quality assurance, and precision manufacturing teams to support round-the-clock assembly operations.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Product Line Diversification:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Scaling its current product line from small-to-medium multirotor motors up to heavy-lift propulsion systems capable of powering large-scale cargo drones and loitering munitions.</span></li>
</ol>
<div>
<div data-test-render-count="1">
<div class="group">
<div class="contents">
<div class="group relative relative pb-3" data-is-streaming="false">
<div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8">
<div>
<div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Westmag&#8217;s proprietary manufacturing process introduces tight aerospace-grade quality controls to a component category historically treated as a cheap commodity. By utilising in-line digital inspection and automated testing jigs, Westmag ensures that every motor leaving the factory floor features a fully traceable digital twin, documenting exact thermal characteristics and performance metrics under maximum load conditions.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Macro View: Securing Dual-Use Tech</span></h2>
<p>Institutional investors are increasingly backing dual-use hardware companies serving both commercial enterprise markets and national security agencies. Demand for reliable, American-made drone components has reached unprecedented levels, driven by commercial logistics expansion and government procurement mandates like the American Security Drone Act.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Propulsion is the heart of any autonomous aerial platform,&#8221; noted a partner at Shield Capital in a statement regarding the round. &#8220;Westmag&#8217;s unique combination of materials science innovation and automated domestic manufacturing fixes a massive structural gap in our industrial base. They are delivering the exact hardware security that the market is crying out for.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/westmag-raises-11m-to-expand-drone-motor-production/" data-wpel-link="internal">Westmag Raises $11M to Expand Drone Motor Production</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
