					<description><![CDATA[<p>Building an AI-Native Travel and Spend Platform Perk has secured a $300 million private credit facility to accelerate its AI-native travel and spend management platform. The facility was led by</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/perk-secures-300m-credit-facility-ai-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Perk Secures $300M Credit Facility to Accelerate AI Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Building an AI-Native Travel and Spend Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Perk has secured a $300 million private credit facility to accelerate its AI-native travel and spend management platform. The facility was led by Neuberger Specialty Finance, with participation from Blue Owl Capital, Hercules Capital, and Liquidity. It replaces the company’s previous 2024 credit facility on improved terms.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The announcement comes as Perk continues strong growth across its platform. The company surpassed $300 million in </span><a href="https://www.lawinsider.com/dictionary/annualized-revenue" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">annualised revenue</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> in 2025. It also recorded revenue growth of 48 percent during the year. Perk serves more than 12,000 companies globally across travel and spend management.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Perk operates as an integrated platform for travel, expense, invoice, and event management. The company rebranded from TravelPerk in 2025. The shift reflects its broader goal of eliminating what it calls “shadow work,” the manual administrative tasks that slow down business productivity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform uses AI to automate booking, expense processing, and workflow management. It also integrates travel and corporate spend into a single system. This unified approach is designed to reduce inefficiencies across business operations. The company launched its integrated platform in November 2025.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">AI adoption has become central to Perk’s business model. The company reported that gross margins increased from 40 percent to the mid-70 percent range over three years. This improvement has been driven by automation and operational efficiency. The company says AI will continue to support scaling across its platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Perk’s customer base includes more than 12,000 companies worldwide. These include global brands operating across multiple industries. The platform is designed to improve visibility and control over business spending. It also aims to reduce time spent on administrative tasks.</span></p>
<h2><b>Credit Facility Backed by Major Institutional Lenders</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $300 million facility was led by Neuberger Specialty Finance. It included participation from Blue Owl Capital, Hercules Capital, and Liquidity. The structure is one of the larger private credit deals completed by a technology company in recent years.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new facility replaces Perk’s $134 million credit arrangement from 2024. It provides improved financing terms and greater flexibility. The capital will be used to expand product development and AI capabilities. It will also support the company’s upcoming US platform rollout.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Lenders highlighted Perk’s strong performance and business model. They cited its growth trajectory and unit economics as key strengths. Institutional investors view the company as well positioned in a large global market. The transaction reflects growing confidence in AI-native enterprise software platforms.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Neuberger Specialty Finance said Perk is well placed to transform corporate travel and spend management. Blue Owl Capital also reaffirmed its support for the company’s long-term strategy. Liquidity noted Perk’s combination of growth and profitability potential. The deal signals strong institutional backing for the company’s expansion plans.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growth Strategy and AI-Driven Expansion<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202317" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202317" class="size-full wp-image-202317" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-with_Y_iPmcqxUlKdaDu-y7YmTg_3pln4ID-Sp2wWSLA0C4k9w.png" alt="AI-powered enterprise platform unifying travel, expense, and workflow management with global expansion network." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202317" class="wp-caption-text">Perk accelerates its AI roadmap to unify business travel and spend management while expanding globally. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Perk plans to use the new funding to accelerate its AI roadmap. The company will invest in product innovation and platform development. It also aims to expand its global footprint, particularly in the United States. The US launch is a key part of its next growth phase.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s leadership has emphasised AI as a core growth driver. CFO Roy Hefer said AI has significantly improved gross margins and operational efficiency. He noted that automation has helped the company scale while maintaining customer experience. Continued AI integration is expected to support further growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Perk’s platform is designed to eliminate fragmented workflows across business operations. It combines travel booking, expense management, and event coordination. This reduces reliance on multiple tools and manual processes. The company believes this unified approach creates long-term customer value.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company was founded in 2015 and has grown into a global SaaS provider. It operates from offices in London and Boston. Its platform is used by organisations across Europe, North America, and other regions. The latest funding positions Perk for continued international expansion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/701x-raises-10m-series-b-cattle-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">701x Raises $10M+ Series B to Expand Cattle Tech Ecosystem</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Market Position and Industry Outlook</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Perk operates in the rapidly growing travel and spend management sector. The market has shifted toward integrated and AI-driven platforms. Companies are increasingly looking to reduce operational inefficiencies. This trend has supported demand for Perk’s unified solution. The company competes with traditional travel management and expense software providers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, its AI-native architecture differentiates it from legacy systems. The platform is designed for automation rather than manual input. This positions Perk in a strong competitive segment of enterprise software. Investors are viewing Perk as part of a greater shift within business operations software. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Automation and the integration of AI are transforming workflows within enterprises, and Perk&#8217;s rise exemplifies the growing need for software that will reduce the time companies spend dealing with back-office administrative tasks.  The company&#8217;s growth strategy is built around this ever-increasing trend in the industry. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $300 million credit facility gives the company additional runway to scale its operations. This additional capital can also be leveraged for future long-term product development initiatives. Perk&#8217;s consistently high revenue growth and expanding profit margins will surely continue to be attractive to institutional investors as the company aims to expand its AI platform worldwide.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
